- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): One of the latent variable modeling problems addressed in the paper is community detection in social networks, which falls under this sub-category.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses optimization of multilinear operations in stochastic gradient descent, which is a common algorithmic technique in machine learning and optimization.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The other latent variable modeling problem addressed in the paper is topic modeling of text articles, which is a common task in information retrieval and natural language processing.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The topic modeling problem also falls under this sub-category, as it involves analyzing and modeling natural language data.
